---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Contact — Online Marketing Directory"
  description="Get in touch with the Online Marketing Directory team. We welcome feedback, questions, and partnership inquiries."
>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p class="legal-meta">We'd love to hear from you.</p>

  <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
  <p>
    Have a question about a tool or training program? Found an error in one of our reviews?
    Want to suggest a tool for us to review? We welcome all feedback and inquiries.
  </p>

  <p>
    You can reach us at: <a href="mailto:hello@onlinemarketingdirectory.com">hello@onlinemarketingdirectory.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to respond to all emails within 2–3 business days. Please note that we receive a high
    volume of messages, so we may not be able to respond to every inquiry individually.
  </p>

  <h2>Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I submit my tool to be listed in the directory?</h3>
  <p>
    We evaluate all tools ourselves before listing them. If you'd like to suggest a tool for
    review, email us with details about the product and we'll consider it for a future review.
    Please note that we do not accept payment for listings or positive reviews.
  </p>

  <h3>Do you offer sponsored content or advertising?</h3>
  <p>
    We do not currently offer sponsored posts or paid placements. Our reviews are editorially
    independent. We participate in affiliate programs, but these do not influence our editorial
    content.
  </p>

  <h3>I found an error in a review. How do I report it?</h3>
  <p>
    Please email us with the specific information that needs to be corrected and a source
    confirming the accurate information. We take accuracy seriously and will investigate
    and correct errors promptly.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use content from this site?</h3>
  <p>
    All content on this site is copyright Online Marketing Directory. For permission to
    reproduce content, please contact us. Brief quotations with attribution and a link back
    to the original page are generally acceptable.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
